 and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Guy de Boubers was born in 1232. He had at least 1 daughter with Isabeau d'Auxy. He died in 1278, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1232–1278":"1232–1278","1235–1290":"1235–1290","1255–1301":"1255–1301","1301":"1301","1235":"1235","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1232":"1232","1290":"1290","Roye, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Roye, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1232–1278":"1232–1278","1235–1290":"1235–1290","1255–1301":"1255–1301","1301":"1301","1235":"1235","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1232":"1232","1290":"1290","Roye, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Roye, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Ranska"},"fr":{"1232–1278":"1232–1278","1235–1290":"1235–1290","1255–1301":"1255–1301","1301":"1301","1235":"1235","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1232":"1232","1290":"1290","Roye, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Roye, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France","lifeSummary":"Guy de Boubers est né en 1232. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Isabeau d'Auxy. Il est décédé en 1278, à l’âge de 46 ans."},"de":{"1232–1278":"1232–1278","1235–1290":"1235–1290","1255–1301":"1255–1301","1301":"1301","1235":"1235","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1232":"1232","1290":"1290","Roye, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Roye, Haute-Saône, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Guy de Bo